b'' b"and the lord's servant must not quarrel; instead, he must be kind to everyone," b'able to teach, not resentful. those who oppose him he must gently instruct, in' b'the hope that god will grant them repentance leading them to a knowledge of the' b'truth, and that they will come to their senses and escape from the trap of the' b'devil, who has taken them captive to do his will.' b'iitimothy 